1
00:00:01,245 --> 00:00:03,145
     [bird tweeting]

2
00:00:03,269 --> 00:00:05,204
    Twilight: I have to admit
     I was a little shocked

3
00:00:05,306 --> 00:00:06,639
         when Princess
        Celestia told me

4
00:00:06,740 --> 00:00:08,973
   she wanted to start a
   Scholastic Buckball league,

5
00:00:09,076 --> 00:00:10,876
      but I was even more
    surprised that she wanted

6
00:00:10,978 --> 00:00:13,779
  the first game to be between
   her school and ours!

7
00:00:13,981 --> 00:00:16,481
Apparently, she's
a huge sportsfan.

8
00:00:16,583 --> 00:00:18,684
       I always thought Celestia
       was kind of a jock.

9
00:00:18,786 --> 00:00:20,785
                Just with really
                wavy hair.

10
00:00:22,055 --> 00:00:23,722
        Anyway, we don't
         have much time.

11
00:00:23,824 --> 00:00:25,157
          The game is in
           two weeks!

12
00:00:25,459 --> 00:00:28,160
      And I want all of YOU
      to coach the team!

13
00:00:28,362 --> 00:00:30,395
               [excited chatter]

14
00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:31,763
            [gasping]

15
00:00:31,865 --> 00:00:33,032
      I know how you feel.

16
00:00:33,234 --> 00:00:35,167
Young athletes ready
to take the field...

17
00:00:35,269 --> 00:00:38,036
   Ooh! You can almost
   breathe in the excitement!

18
00:00:38,938 --> 00:00:39,570
             [gasp]

19
00:00:40,007 --> 00:00:42,841
I don't think you should
breathe it in so hard!

20
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:44,776
            [splash]

21
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:48,380
       It's just... two
       weeks doesn't feel

22
00:00:48,482 --> 00:00:51,750
    like a whole lot of time
    to train a <i>whole team</i>.

23
00:00:52,052 --> 00:00:53,518
                 Maybe the
                 School of Magic

24
00:00:53,620 --> 00:00:55,053
            could play a few
            other schools first.

25
00:00:55,155 --> 00:00:56,688
           Like the Mane and
           Tail Styling College,

26
00:00:56,790 --> 00:00:58,357
            or the Scroll-Making
            Institute?

27
00:00:58,559 --> 00:01:00,592
             Relax. You're
             gonna do just fine.

28
00:01:00,694 --> 00:01:03,562
Um... what makes
you so sure?

29
00:01:03,664 --> 00:01:05,897
      Because I have faith
        in my friends...

30
00:01:06,099 --> 00:01:07,732
           who also
          happen to be..

31
00:01:07,834 --> 00:01:10,469
      the best buckball
      players in Equestria!

32
00:01:10,771 --> 00:01:12,504
            Oh, yeah!

33
00:01:12,606 --> 00:01:24,478
               ♪♪

34
00:01:24,585 --> 00:01:26,752
      I guess that is
      sort of true.

35
00:01:27,054 --> 00:01:28,820
       I asked Rainbow
        Dash to help too.

36
00:01:28,922 --> 00:01:29,755
        But I'm not sure
         where she...

37
00:01:29,857 --> 00:01:30,922
             [zoom]

38
00:01:31,024 --> 00:01:32,758
    Sorry I'm late! But when
    Twilight said she needed

39
00:01:32,860 --> 00:01:34,059
        my help with the
        buckball team,

40
00:01:34,161 --> 00:01:35,627
      I figured I'd better
      grab every piece of

41
00:01:35,729 --> 00:01:37,429
       coaching equipment
        I could find!

42
00:01:39,266 --> 00:01:40,832
         So, what should
         I focus on?

43
00:01:40,934 --> 00:01:43,235
        Offense? Defense?
          Trick plays?

44
00:01:43,637 --> 00:01:46,105
I was thinking of something
even more important!

45
00:01:46,207 --> 00:01:48,540
       Awesome! Lay it on
       me! Whatever it is,

46
00:01:48,842 --> 00:01:51,243
     I'll give it a hundred
     and twenty percent!

47
00:01:51,345 --> 00:01:53,545
      I knew I could count
       on your enthusiasm!

48
00:01:53,647 --> 00:01:57,049
    That's why I want you to
    coach.. the Cheer Squad!

49
00:01:57,851 --> 00:01:58,516
             [thud]

50
00:01:58,618 --> 00:02:00,385
        [bouncing balls]

51
00:02:00,487 --> 00:02:01,986
          CHEERLEADING?

52
00:02:41,562 --> 00:02:46,598
               ♪♪

53
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:48,967
              I don't mean to
               sound ungrateful...

54
00:02:49,069 --> 00:02:50,536
      It's just, when you
     said you wanted my help

55
00:02:50,638 --> 00:02:52,671
    with something important,
     I thought you meant...

56
00:02:52,973 --> 00:02:54,606
      something important.

57
00:02:54,708 --> 00:02:56,842
         The Cheer Squad
          IS important.

58
00:02:57,444 --> 00:03:01,380
                  Bah-ha-ha! Oh.

59
00:03:01,482 --> 00:03:04,182
Well, sure Cheer Squad
is <i>totally</i> important

60
00:03:04,284 --> 00:03:05,951
to somepony
who isn't me,

61
00:03:06,053 --> 00:03:08,520
but I'm more about ponies
playing <i>in</i> the game,

62
00:03:08,622 --> 00:03:09,955
not cheering for it.

63
00:03:10,157 --> 00:03:12,658
         [laughter]

64
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:14,126
I mean, it's great
that someponies

65
00:03:14,228 --> 00:03:16,995
only want to cheer, though I
don't know why they would.

66
00:03:17,097 --> 00:03:20,098
       Hm. Well, maybe this will
       be a good opportunity

67
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:21,433
            for you to find out.

68
00:03:21,735 --> 00:03:24,036
       Of course I've seen
      cheer squads before...

69
00:03:24,138 --> 00:03:25,071
        On the sidelines...

70
00:03:25,172 --> 00:03:27,805
   But I'm not even a hundred
   percent sure what they do.

71
00:03:27,908 --> 00:03:29,241
        I'll probably
        just mess it up.

72
00:03:29,443 --> 00:03:31,210
               I think you might
               be surprised.

73
00:03:31,412 --> 00:03:33,512
               In fact, I'm more
               sure than ever

74
00:03:33,614 --> 00:03:35,413
                 that you're the
                 perfect choice!

75
00:03:36,684 --> 00:03:40,686
I'm actually 120
percent sure!

76
00:03:40,788 --> 00:03:42,588
         And it's a good
           thing too...

77
00:03:42,690 --> 00:03:45,524
        The cheer squad
        REALLY needs you.

78
00:03:45,726 --> 00:03:46,892
What do you mean?

79
00:03:46,994 --> 00:03:50,395
   Well, I've been helping out
   and let's put it this way.

80
00:03:50,497 --> 00:03:52,798
       We've got two weeks
       until the big game

81
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:55,534
        and.. we could
         use two years...

82
00:03:55,736 --> 00:03:58,003
         But that's all
          gonna change

83
00:03:58,205 --> 00:04:01,907
       because you're here
      to save the day!

84
00:04:02,309 --> 00:04:05,911
Oh...kay. So why
are <i>you</i> here?

85
00:04:06,113 --> 00:04:08,413
             What, a pony can't
             show school spirit?

86
00:04:08,515 --> 00:04:10,349
You don't even go
to this school.

87
00:04:10,551 --> 00:04:13,986
    Ah OK, when I went to the
     Buckball Hall of Fame,

88
00:04:14,688 --> 00:04:18,257
     I found out buckball
     souvenirs are BIG bits!

89
00:04:18,359 --> 00:04:20,059
          If Twilight's
         team does well,

90
00:04:20,161 --> 00:04:22,862
    I can start selling them
     full time in Ponyville,

91
00:04:23,364 --> 00:04:25,898
                 so <i>I</i> have a
                 vested interest

92
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:29,168
                and <i>you</i> have an
                assistant coach!

93
00:04:29,370 --> 00:04:30,602
                 [whistle tweet]

94
00:04:30,704 --> 00:04:31,670
     [groan]

95
00:04:31,772 --> 00:04:33,738
        [excited chatter]

96
00:04:33,807 --> 00:04:34,873
She's here!

97
00:04:34,975 --> 00:04:36,208
                 Get the lights!

98
00:04:37,010 --> 00:04:37,777
        [lights click on]

99
00:04:38,779 --> 00:04:41,580
        <i> Over, and over,</i>
        <i> and over again!</i>

100
00:04:41,682 --> 00:04:43,549
         <i> We wanna dance</i>
         <i> for each other</i>

101
00:04:43,651 --> 00:04:45,317
         <i> and for all of</i>
        <i> our friends!</i>

102
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:47,820
                 Dancing. Right.

103
00:04:48,122 --> 00:04:50,422
    I've seen you two around
    school, haven't I?

104
00:04:50,524 --> 00:04:53,959
      [giggle] I'm Shimmy Shake, and
      this is Lighthoof!

105
00:04:54,061 --> 00:04:56,828
         And we are your
          lead dancers!

106
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:01,833
            I didn't know you
            three would be here...

107
00:05:02,035 --> 00:05:02,934
   [giggle]

108
00:05:03,036 --> 00:05:05,504
       Yona want to cheer
     and make pony pyramid!

109
00:05:05,606 --> 00:05:07,339
           [crashing]

110
00:05:07,941 --> 00:05:09,508
       And I thought this
       could be my chance

111
00:05:09,610 --> 00:05:11,977
      to make an impression
       on everypony!

112
00:05:12,379 --> 00:05:14,947
   You know, for something
   other than changing shape...

113
00:05:15,649 --> 00:05:18,550
    I didn't realize you were
    into school spirit, Smolder.

114
00:05:18,752 --> 00:05:21,586
Uh, I just came with these
two. Guess they think

115
00:05:21,688 --> 00:05:23,889
     you can make cheer
    squad cool or something...

116
00:05:24,091 --> 00:05:25,490
              Don't count on it.

117
00:05:26,627 --> 00:05:29,361
     OK, now that we're all
     here, why don't you

118
00:05:29,463 --> 00:05:31,730
      tell us the plan? How
      are you gonna make

119
00:05:31,832 --> 00:05:35,301
    us into the most awesome
    cheer squad ever!?

120
00:05:36,103 --> 00:05:37,870
          Uh, I dunno.

121
00:05:38,772 --> 00:05:40,139
[disappointed sighs]

122
00:05:40,241 --> 00:05:42,674
    I mean, if you guys were
    an actual buckball team,

123
00:05:42,779 --> 00:05:44,462
    I'd have plenty of ideas,

124
00:05:45,363 --> 00:05:47,446
    but I don't know anything
    about cheerleading.

125
00:05:47,948 --> 00:05:50,949
         Oh, ha-ha, yes.
        Good one, coach!

126
00:05:51,051 --> 00:05:53,652
      But Headmare Twilight
     picked you for the job,

127
00:05:53,754 --> 00:05:57,823
     so I'm pretty sure you
     know what you're doing.

128
00:05:58,125 --> 00:05:59,391
         If you say so...

129
00:05:59,893 --> 00:06:02,894
          Ha-ha. Right.
          OK, gang.

130
00:06:02,996 --> 00:06:05,731
   Let's show Rainbow Dash
   what we've been working on

131
00:06:05,833 --> 00:06:07,933
        and she can take
         it from there.

132
00:06:08,035 --> 00:06:09,100
    Cheer Squad can do that!

133
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:10,769
           [crashing]

134
00:06:10,871 --> 00:06:13,672
Yep! All we need
is a little music!

135
00:06:14,674 --> 00:06:16,742
             <i> ♪♪</i>

136
00:06:16,844 --> 00:06:21,580
       <i> Over, and ove-wah!</i>
       <i> and ove-wah! again!</i>

137
00:06:21,682 --> 00:06:22,981
           [crashing]

138
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:25,951
         <i> We wanna dance....</i>
         <i> for each other</i>

139
00:06:26,053 --> 00:06:27,986
         <i> and for all of</i>
          <i> our fri-ahhh</i>

140
00:06:28,088 --> 00:06:29,654
               ♪♪

141
00:06:29,756 --> 00:06:32,791
2, 4, 6, 8.

142
00:06:34,295 --> 00:06:37,396
     [quietly] <i> ...Friendship School</i>
      <i> is really great...</i>

143
00:06:37,498 --> 00:06:39,197
               ♪♪

144
00:06:39,299 --> 00:06:40,299
            [whoosh]

145
00:06:40,401 --> 00:06:41,566
           [crashing]

146
00:06:41,668 --> 00:06:43,702
        [breaking glass]

147
00:06:44,004 --> 00:06:46,038
         Well, that was
           a disaster.

148
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:47,973
     It's kind of hard to
    stick to our choreography

149
00:06:48,075 --> 00:06:49,541
         when the floor
           is moving.

150
00:06:49,943 --> 00:06:53,445
   Yeah, Yona. Your stomps
   are a little <i>too</i> powerful.

151
00:06:53,547 --> 00:06:55,681
Can we make pony
pyramid instead?

152
00:06:55,883 --> 00:06:57,249
         Maybe we should
           figure out

153
00:06:57,351 --> 00:06:59,051
         which cheers we
        should do first.

154
00:06:59,153 --> 00:07:02,221
Tss. Yeah. Because that'll
fix everything...

155
00:07:02,423 --> 00:07:06,591
    So.. I mean there's a few,
     uh, a lot of problems,

156
00:07:06,693 --> 00:07:09,094
      but nothing you
       can't solve. Right?

157
00:07:09,196 --> 00:07:10,729
                  Huh? Oh. Yeah.

158
00:07:10,831 --> 00:07:13,298
     Listen, you guys don't have
     anything to worry about.

159
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:14,433
     We don't?

160
00:07:14,635 --> 00:07:17,436
Nope. In fact, I think
what you all just did

161
00:07:17,538 --> 00:07:20,272
is totally fine. You
guys have got this!

162
00:07:20,374 --> 00:07:22,708
So... I'm just gonna
head down to the field.

163
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:24,809
                 Great practice,
                   everypony!

164
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,046
             [slam]

165
00:07:31,218 --> 00:07:33,118
               ♪♪

166
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:35,187
          Oof! What are
           you doing!?

167
00:07:35,689 --> 00:07:37,622
What are YOU doing?

168
00:07:37,724 --> 00:07:40,225
You gotta come back
and coach the Squad!

169
00:07:41,295 --> 00:07:44,162
    I watched some cheer
    stuff. Looked fine to me.

170
00:07:44,764 --> 00:07:47,599
          Well, it's not! Do you
          know what'll happen

171
00:07:47,701 --> 00:07:50,301
       if they do what they
       just did at the big game?

172
00:07:50,803 --> 00:07:52,237
         Uh... nothing?

173
00:07:52,339 --> 00:07:54,139
            Uh wrong!

174
00:07:54,441 --> 00:07:55,207
              Oooh!

175
00:07:55,409 --> 00:07:58,643
A good cheer squad
gets the fans excited,

176
00:07:58,745 --> 00:08:00,612
which gets the
team excited.

177
00:08:00,814 --> 00:08:02,748
But if nopony's
excited,

178
00:08:02,850 --> 00:08:06,918
then nopony.. buys..
any.... SOUVENIERS!

179
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:10,455
   I THINK you're blowing this
   a little out of proportion!

180
00:08:10,557 --> 00:08:13,592
      Point is, if I'm
     going to make any bits

181
00:08:13,694 --> 00:08:16,762
    at these games, that
    squad has to get better!

182
00:08:16,864 --> 00:08:19,964
        And to do that,
       they need a <i>coach</i>!

183
00:08:20,868 --> 00:08:24,503
    You know what? You're
   right! Why don't you do it?

184
00:08:24,605 --> 00:08:27,438
     I mean <i>you're</i> the one
     with a vested interest!

185
00:08:30,611 --> 00:08:32,911
      The trick to being a
      good buckball keeper

186
00:08:33,013 --> 00:08:34,746
        is to do nothing.

187
00:08:34,848 --> 00:08:39,484
      Just empty your
       mind. Be the ball!

188
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:42,821
         Uh, balls don't
           have minds.

189
00:08:43,123 --> 00:08:44,689
            Exactly.

190
00:08:46,093 --> 00:08:51,496
               ♪♪

191
00:08:51,798 --> 00:08:52,798
Where's my
blindfol-

192
00:08:52,900 --> 00:08:56,432
     <i> My turn!</i>
                                   <i> I wanna do that!</i>
      <i> Come on! Over here!</i>

193
00:08:56,537 --> 00:08:58,870
          Why are you watching
          Snail's weird practice

194
00:08:58,972 --> 00:09:01,240
         when you're supposed to
         be practicing with us?

195
00:09:01,342 --> 00:09:04,410
Heh heh. Snail's practice
is definitely weird.

196
00:09:04,912 --> 00:09:07,612
Uh, I thought Snips was
practicing with you.

197
00:09:07,814 --> 00:09:09,114
                    He <i>was</i>...

198
00:09:10,317 --> 00:09:12,451
       Uh. Do you have any
       idea how hard it is

199
00:09:12,553 --> 00:09:14,053
     to dance in this stuff?

200
00:09:14,455 --> 00:09:16,555
     Plus all these buttons
       jingle so much,

201
00:09:16,657 --> 00:09:18,290
         you can't hear
         my cheers.

202
00:09:18,592 --> 00:09:20,259
               Speaking up might
                help a little.

203
00:09:20,561 --> 00:09:22,728
So don't dance
and cheer...

204
00:09:22,930 --> 00:09:25,797
          Uh, then what
         Cheer Squad do?

205
00:09:26,099 --> 00:09:26,765
          I don't know.

206
00:09:26,867 --> 00:09:27,933
               Maybe you should!

207
00:09:28,035 --> 00:09:30,335
               ...or whatever.
               You're the coach!

208
00:09:30,437 --> 00:09:32,871
      You're supposed to come up
      with stuff for us to do.

209
00:09:33,073 --> 00:09:36,674
OK.... I've got something
for you to do.

210
00:09:37,178 --> 00:09:43,882
   Just do nothing. Empty
    your minds. Be the squad.

211
00:09:43,984 --> 00:09:46,017
               We <i>are</i> the squad.

212
00:09:46,319 --> 00:09:47,352
            Oh, yeah.

213
00:09:47,554 --> 00:09:50,755
    At least helping sell my
    souvenirs was.. something.

214
00:09:53,927 --> 00:09:57,530
    Yona still not understand
    how this make us better.

215
00:09:58,632 --> 00:10:02,568
    Huh?! Professor Dash
    needs to stay and coach!

216
00:10:03,070 --> 00:10:05,570
    Ugh. You guys asked me
    to come up with something

217
00:10:05,672 --> 00:10:06,838
           and I did.

218
00:10:07,140 --> 00:10:08,907
I don't think
"nothing" counts.

219
00:10:09,209 --> 00:10:10,676
     Then I'm out of ideas!

220
00:10:11,278 --> 00:10:13,778
              This is the School
              of Friendship.

221
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,714
              If you need ideas,

222
00:10:15,816 --> 00:10:18,450
             you should ask your
             friends for help.

223
00:10:19,352 --> 00:10:20,418
            Fine.

224
00:10:20,820 --> 00:10:22,153
♪♪

225
00:10:22,255 --> 00:10:25,023
      [no audible dialogue]

226
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:42,197
♪♪

227
00:10:42,342 --> 00:10:45,944
     OK, since you guys have
    been nagging me non-stop

228
00:10:46,046 --> 00:10:48,914
      about this cheer
     stuff for, like, <i>ever</i>...

229
00:10:49,016 --> 00:10:50,816
It has literally
been one day.

230
00:10:51,018 --> 00:10:53,151
      I went around and got
      everything you need.

231
00:10:53,253 --> 00:10:57,956
               ♪♪

232
00:10:58,058 --> 00:11:00,259
     Uh, what are we
    supposed to do with hay?

233
00:11:00,461 --> 00:11:02,961
 Beats me, but Applejack
  seemed pretty sure about it.

234
00:11:03,163 --> 00:11:04,462
      Oh! I almost forgot.

235
00:11:05,799 --> 00:11:07,599
      A rhyming dictionary?

236
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:10,502
    Yeah. Zecora's a lot less
    helpful then you'd think.

237
00:11:10,604 --> 00:11:13,004
  That's from the library so
  you can come up with cheers.

238
00:11:13,206 --> 00:11:14,806
       OK! Good practice.

239
00:11:15,108 --> 00:11:17,009
         So, you're just
         leaving again?

240
